text: Skora Building, also known as the Budlock Building, was a historic commercial building located in downtown Evansville, Indiana, USA. It was built between 1911 and 1913 and was a two-story, rectangular brick building. Note: This includes , and accompanying photographs It has been demolished. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1982 and delisted in 2009. ==References== Category:Former National Register of Historic Places in Indiana Category:Commercial buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Indiana Category:Commercial buildings completed in 1913 Category:Buildings and structures in Evansville, Indiana Category:National Register of Historic Places in Evansville, Indiana
